                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>               “I wish I could have had more stories featured. More material,” she replied.</p>
<p>               I mention that it’s always easy to want more time. She shrugs.</p>
<p>               “Yeah. But I think by the time I figured out what I wanted more or less, or at least the concept, I would have liked more time.”</p>
<p>               Patiño smiled as she shook my hand. I walked to the door, expecting to see her packing up too, but she turned back to the exhibit. When she saw me looking, she smiled again.</p>
<p>               “I’ll spend a little bit more time here.”</p>
<p><i>The online portion of the exhibit can be viewed online at <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://stories-of-lynn.com/">http://stories-of-lynn.com/</a></i></p>
<p><i>Andrea Patiño’s personal website can be found at http://www.andreapatino.com/</i></p>
